[src:fast-exponentiation/euler-s-totient-function] The following property, which is unpublished as a specific result but has long been known, has important consequences.
[src:fast-exponentiation/euler-s-totient-function] For instance it rules out uniform distribution of the values of $\varphi (n)$ in the arithmetic progressions modulo q for any integer $q>1$ .
[src:fast-exponentiation/euler-s-totient-function] This is an elementary consequence of the fact that the sum of the reciprocals of the primes congruent to 1 modulo q diverges, which itself is a corollary of the proof of Dirichlet's theorem on arithmetic progressions.
